  "prompt": "Will a magnet stick to copper?",
  "response": "No, a magnet will not stick to copper. Copper is a non-ferromagnetic metal, which means it does not have the magnetic properties needed to be attracted to a magnet. Magnets are typically attracted to ferromagnetic materials, such as iron, nickel, and cobalt. While copper can interact with magnetic fields in other ways (for example, it can exhibit eddy currents), it will not cling to a magnet.",
